{"title_page": "Vartha", "text_new": "{{short description|1986 film directed by I. V. Sasi}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Vartha\n| image          = Vartha poster.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| film name      = {{Infobox name module|ml|\u0d35\u0d3e\u0d7c\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24}}\n| director       = [[I. V. Sasi]]\n| producer       = [[P. V. Gangadharan]]\n| writer         = [[T. Damodaran]]\n| screenplay     = T. Damodaran\n| starring       = [[Mammootty]]<br />[[Mohanlal]] (cameo)<br />[[Venu Nagavally]]<br />[[Prathapachandran]]\n| music          = [[A. T. Ummer]]<br />'''Lyrics:'''<br />[[Bichu Thirumala]]\n| cinematography = [[Jayanan Vincent]]\n| editing        = [[K. Narayanan]]\n| studio         = Grihalakshmi Productions\n| distributor    = Grihalakshmi Productions\n| released       = {{Film date|1986|2|28|df=y}}\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Malayalam\n}}\n\n'''''Vartha''''' ({{trans|News}}) is a [[Malayalam films of 1986|1986]] [[Cinema of India|Indian]] [[Malayalam language]] film, directed by [[I. V. Sasi]] and produced by P. V. Gangadharan. The film stars [[Mammootty]], [[Mohanlal]] (cameo), [[Venu Nagavally]] and [[Prathapachandran]] in the lead roles. The film has musical score by [[A. T. Ummer]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/movie.php?i=1867 |title=Vaartha |website=Malayala Chalachithram |access-date=22 October 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://malayalasangeetham.info/m.php?1731 |title=Vaartha |website=Malayalasangeetham.info |access-date=22 October 2014}}</ref> The film was successful at the box office.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-fridayreview/architect-of-blockbusters/article4655388.ece |title=Architect of blockbusters |date=26 April 2013 |website=[[The Hindu]]}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/saluting-the-maker-of-super-hits/article4612482.ece |title=Saluting the maker of super hits |date=13 April 2013 |website=[[The Hindu]] |access-date=2019-10-29}}</ref> The film was remade in Tamil as ''[[Palaivana Rojakkal]]'' (1986),<ref name=\"sify\">{{Cite web |url=https://www.sify.com/movies/sibiraj-is-all-set-to-make-it-big-news-tamil-kkfvEFdcfchsi.html |title=Sibiraj is all set to make it big! |date=7 November 2004 |website=[[Sify]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171102181952/http://www.sify.com/movies/sibiraj-is-all-set-to-make-it-big-news-tamil-kkfvEFdcfchsi.html |archive-date=2 November 2017 |access-date=2 November 2017}}</ref> and in [[Hindi]] as ''[[Jai Shiv Shankar]]'', which never released.\n\n== Cast ==\n{{colbegin|colwidth=}}\n*[[Mammootty]] as Madhavan Kutty\n*[[Mohanlal]] as Parol Vasu (Cameo)\n*[[Rahman (actor)|Rahman]] as Unnikrishnan\n*[[Seema (actress)|Seema]] as Radha Menon\n*[[Nalini (actress)|Nalini]] as Vasanthi\n*[[Venu Nagavally]] as Devan\n*[[Prathapachandran]] as Nambeeshan\n*[[Devan (actor)|Devan]] as Philip\n*[[T. G. Ravi]] as Manikyam Kumar\n*[[Janardhanan (actor)|Janardhanan]] as James\n*[[K. P. A. C. Lalitha]] as Kunjulakshmi\n*[[Jagannatha Varma]] as Kurup\n*[[Babu Namboothiri]] as Venu\n*[[Thikkurissi Sukumaran Nair]] as Keshavan Nair\n*[[K. P. A. C. Sunny]] as Enforcement Officer\n*[[K. P. A. C. Azeez]] as City Police Commissioner\n*[[Balan K. Nair]] as Forest Minister\n*[[Kuthiravattam Pappu]] as Hamsa\n*[[Kundara Johny]] as Francis\n*[[Paravoor Bharathan]] as Bharathan\n*[[Kunjandi]] as Pachu Pillai\n*[[Nellikode Bhaskaran]] as Radha's Relative\n{{colend}}\n\n== Soundtrack ==\nThe music was composed by [[A. T. Ummer]] and the lyrics were written by [[Bichu Thirumala]].\n\n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCF\" align=\"centre\"\n| '''No.''' || '''Song''' || '''Singers''' ||'''Lyrics''' || '''Length (m:ss)'''\n|-\n| 1 || \"Innalekal\" || [[K. J. Yesudas]] || [[Bichu Thirumala]] ||\n|-\n| 2 || \"Salilam Sruthisaagaram\" || K. J. Yesudas, Ashalatha || Bichu Thirumala ||\n|}\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|0215307|Vartha}}\n{{I. V. Sasi}}\n\n[[Category:1986 films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:1980s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Malayalam films remade in other languages]]\n[[Category:Films directed by I. V. Sasi]]\n\n\n{{1980s-Malayalam-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1986 film directed by I. V. Sasi}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=February 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Vartha\n| image          = Vartha poster.jpg\n| caption        = Poster\n| film name      = {{Infobox name module|ml|\u0d35\u0d3e\u0d7c\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24}}\n| director       = [[I. V. Sasi]]\n| producer       = [[P. V. Gangadharan]]\n| writer         = [[T. Damodaran]]\n| screenplay     = T. Damodaran\n| starring       = [[Mammootty]]<br />[[Mohanlal]] (cameo)<br />[[Venu Nagavally]]<br />[[Prathapachandran]]\n| music          = [[A. T. Ummer]]<br />'''Lyrics:'''<br />[[Bichu Thirumala]]\n| cinematography = [[Jayanan Vincent]]\n| editing        = [[K. Narayanan]]\n| studio         = Grihalakshmi Productions\n| distributor    = Grihalakshmi Productions\n| released       = {{Film date|1986|2|28|df=y}}\n| country        = [[India]]\n| language       = Malayalam\n}}\n\n'''''Vartha''''' ({{trans|News}}) is a [[Malayalam films of 1986|1986]] [[Cinema of India|Indian]] [[Malayalam language]] film, directed by [[I. V. Sasi]] and produced by P. V. Gangadharan. The film stars [[Mammootty]], [[Mohanlal]] (cameo), [[Venu Nagavally]] and [[Prathapachandran]] in the lead roles. The film has musical score by [[A. T. Ummer]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.malayalachalachithram.com/movie.php?i=1867 |title=Vaartha |website=Malayala Chalachithram |access-dat