{"title_page": "Vadakakku Oru Hridayam", "text_new": "{{short description|1978 film directed by I. V. Sasi}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2015}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=November 2015}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Vadakakku Oru Hridayam\n| image          = Vadakakkoru Hridayam.jpg\n| caption        = A Heart for Hire\n| director       = [[I. V. Sasi]]\n| producer       = Hari Pothan\n| screenplay     = [[Padmarajan]]\n| based on       = {{based on|''Vadakakkoru Hridayam''|Padmarajan}}\n| starring       = [[Jayabharathi]]<br>[[Madhu (actor)|Madhu]]<br>[[M. G. Soman|Soman]]<br>[[Raghavan (actor)|Raghavan]]\n| music          = [[Devarajan]]\n| cinematography = [[Ramachandra Babu]]\n| editing        = [[K. Narayanan]]\n| studio         = Supriya Creations\n| distributor    =  Navasakthi<br>Ajantha\n| released       = {{Film date|1978|6|15|df=y}}\n| runtime        =\n| country        = India\n| language       = Malayalam\n| budget         =\n| gross          =\n}}\n\n'''''Vadakakku Oru Hridayam''''' ({{lang-en|A Heart for Hire}}) is a 1978 [[Malayalam]] film directed by [[I. V. Sasi]] and written by [[Padmarajan]]. The film is based on the novel of the same name written by Padmarajan. It stars [[Jayabharathi]], [[Madhu (actor)|Madhu]], [[M. G. Soman|Soman]] and [[Raghavan (actor)|Raghavan]] in the lead roles. It was dubbed and released in Hindi as ''Man Ka Aangan''.<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?ei=Nwz-TcLCBYiCvgOfvvGgAw&ct=result&id=WHpTAAAAYAAJ&dq=Vadakakkoru+Hridayam&q=Vadakakkoru+Hrudayam \"Film World article\"]</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nThe film's story revolves around the relationship of a young woman with three different men.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Jayabharathi]] as Aswathi.\n* [[Madhu (actor)|Madhu]] as Sadasivan Pillai, Aswathi's second husband.\n* [[M. G. Soman|Soman]] as Kesavankutty, Aswathi's lover.\n* [[Raghavan (actor)|Raghavan]] as Parameswaran Pillai, Aswathi's first husband.\n* [[Sankaradi]] as Paramu Pillai.\n* [[Adoor Bhasi]] as Kurumba.\n* [[Janardhanan (actor)|Janardhanan]] as Aswathi's brother.\n* [[Bahadoor]]  as Aswathi's father.\n* [[Sukumari]] as Paramu Pillai's wife.\n* [[Adoor Bhavani]] as Karthyayani.\n* [[Kanakadurga]] as Malini.\n* [[Reena (actress)|Reena]].\n\n==Soundtrack== \nThe music was composed by [[G. Devarajan]] and the lyrics were written by [[Kavalam Narayana Panicker]]. \n{| border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\" \n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCF\" align=\"center\" \n| '''No.''' || '''Song''' || '''Singers''' ||'''Lyrics''' || '''Length (m:ss)''' \n|- \n| 1 || \"Ozhinja Veedin\" || [[K. J. Yesudas]] || [[Kavalam Narayana Panicker]] || \n|- \n| 2 || \"Painkuraalippashuvin\" || [[P. Madhuri]] || Kavalam Narayana Panicker || \n|- \n| 3 || \"Poovaamkuzhali\" || [[K. J. Yesudas]], Chorus || Kavalam Narayana Panicker || \n|- \n| 4 || \"Theyyaathi Nunthinuntho\" || [[P. Jayachandran]], P. Madhuri, Chorus || Kavalam Narayana Panicker || \n|}\n\n==Box office==\nThe film was both a critical and commercial success.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/he-reigned-at-box-office-but-made-classics-too/article19912969.ece/amp/|title=I.V. Sasi reigned at the box office, and made classics too|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=24 October 2017}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDB title|0267080}}\n* [http://www.malayalasangeetham.info/mmdb/57 ''Vadakakkoru Hridayam''] at the Malayalam Movie Database\n\n{{Padmarajan}}\n\n{{I. V. Sasi}}\n\n[[Category:1970s Malayalam-language films]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Films based on Indian novels]]\n[[Category:Indian erotic films]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Padmarajan]]\n[[Category:Films directed by I. V. Sasi]]\n\n\n{{1970s-Malayalam-film-stub}}\n{{erotic-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1978 film directed by I. V. Sasi}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 201